Crataeva Tapia
Jouvea pilosa
habitat: In open, level to slightly sloping areas favored by the terns for nesting, near the beach; surrounded by low forest consisting almost entirely of Crataeva tapia (3-4 m tall), Porous soil.
locality: Isabel Island, E of Tres Marias Is. Volcanic islet--cormorant and tern breeding ground.
